rules.ruleString: Must be enrolled in course version {0101, M5010}

description: All aspects of human pregnancy from implantation to the puerperium. Unit taught by both basic and clinical scientists, thereby affording the student an appreciation of the close integration between the disciplines. The module will be taught in four sections: implantation and placentation, the foetus, the mother and politics of pregnancy.
faculty: Faculty of Medicine, Nursing and Health Sciences
